      • setCurrentLocation

        public RouteManager.UpdatedRouteOptions setCurrentLocation(GeoPoint point)
        Sets the current location along the route.

        Specifying this parameter will return only information from this point to the end of the route, with the exception of Route.getPoints(), Route.getSpeedBuckets(), and Route.getBoundingBox().

        Parameters:
        point - The current location.
        Returns:
        This instance of the RouteManager.UpdatedRouteOptions class.
        Throws:
        RouteManager.RouteManagerException - when the point is invalid.

      • setReturnBetterRoute

        public RouteManager.UpdatedRouteOptions setReturnBetterRoute(boolean returnBetterRoute)
        Set whether or not to return a better route from the current location if available. Note that this will be ignored if the current location has not been set.
        Parameters:
        returnBetterRoute - True to get a better route if available, false otherwise.
        Returns:
        This instance of the RouteManager.UpdatedRouteOptions class.
        See Also:
        RouteManager.UpdatedRouteOptions.setCurrentLocation(com.inrix.sdk.model.GeoPoint)

      • setCollapseManeuvers

        public RouteManager.UpdatedRouteOptions setCollapseManeuvers(boolean collapseManeuvers)
        Set the flag to collapse the maneuvers of this route response.
        Parameters:
        collapseManeuvers - If true, minor maneuvers are collapsed into one. If false, no maneuvers are collapsed.
        Returns:
        This instance of the RouteManager.UpdatedRouteOptions class.
